 {"id":"bd-mblr.1.2","title":"Test Realism Taxonomy Inventory","description":"Enumerate all existing tests and classify each as mock/double, in-memory backend, file-backed single-process, or full-stack integration. Produce a machine-readable inventory and heatmap by crate/module to identify overreliance on mocks/fakes.","design":"Build taxonomy from static discovery plus small curated overrides, then preserve deterministic serialization for diffs over time.","acceptance_criteria":"- Every existing test target is classified into realism tiers (mock/double, in-memory, file-backed, full-stack).
- Inventory output is machine-readable and queryable by crate/module/path.
