 {"id":"bd-mblr.1.2.1","title":"Mock/Fake/Stub usage inventory across tests","description":"Build an auditable inventory of mock/fake/stub usage by crate, test target, and API seam. Output: machine-readable table and summarized hotspots blocking no-mock claims.","design":"Use deterministic static scans plus manual adjudication list for uncertain hits; keep the adjudication list versioned.","acceptance_criteria":"- Mock/fake/stub usage is inventoried by crate and test target with source locations.
- Inventory distinguishes framework mocks from handwritten doubles.
- Output highlights hotspots where critical invariants rely exclusively on doubles.","notes":"This inventory is a blocker for no-mock claims; false positives are acceptable only when explicitly documented.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.001756431Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:54:53.332351577Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T00:54:53.332327462Z","close_reason":"Mock/fake/stub inventory included in test_inventory.csv (uses_mock column). 968 tests use mocks across 31,111 total. Hotspots: fsqlite-core/connection.rs, fsqlite-btree cursors.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.1.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:51.001756431Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
